ENTRY       EC 1.14.13.174              Enzyme
NAME        averantin hydroxylase;
            AVN hydroxylase;
            avnA (gene name)
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen;
            With NADH or NADPH as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen into the other donor
SYSNAME     (1'S)-averantin,NADPH:O2 oxidoreductase (5'-hydroxylating)
REACTION    (1) (1'S)-averantin + NADPH + H+ + O2 = (1'S,5'S)-5'-hydroxyaverantin + NADP+ + H2O [RN:R10317];
            (2) (1'S)-averantin + NADPH + H+ + O2 = (1'S,5'R)-5'-hydroxyaverantin + NADP+ + H2O [RN:R10318]
ALL_REAC    R10317 R10318
SUBSTRATE   (1'S)-averantin [CPD:C20499];
            NADPH [CPD:C00005];
            H+ [CPD:C00080];
            O2 [CPD:C00007]
PRODUCT     (1'S,5'S)-5'-hydroxyaverantin [CPD:C20500];
            NADP+ [CPD:C00006];
            H2O [CPD:C00001];
            (1'S,5'R)-5'-hydroxyaverantin [CPD:C20501]
COMMENT     A heme-thiolate (P-450) monooxygenase isolated from Aspergillus parasiticus. There is no reaction with (1'R)-averantin. Involved in aflatoxin biosynthesis.
